-- Buy-to-let lender Paragon's first-half profit rises 21 pct
-- By Aastha Agnihotri in Bangalore
-- Tue May 20, 2014 02:15AM EDT
-- None



May 20 (Reuters) - The Paragon Group of Companies Plc <PARA.L>, the parent of buy-to-let lender Paragon Mortgages, reported a 21 percent rise in underlying pretax profit in the first half of its fiscal year, benefiting from increased loan portfolios and demand for buy-to-let loans.

